== List of countries by area harvested for apples ==
This is a list of the top ten countries by area harvested for apples in [[hectares]] (ha). The total area harvested in the world for apples was 4,933,841 hectares in 2017, down 6.8% from 5,293,340 hectares in 2016.<ref>{{citeweb|website=FAOSTAT|title=Crops|url=http://www.fao.org/faostat/en/#data/QC/|access-date=30 April 2019}} Countries - Select All; Regions - World + (Total); Elements - Area harvested; Items - Apples; Years - 2017 + 2016</ref> {| class="wikitable sortable" ! data-sort-type="number" | Rank !! Country !! data-sort-type="number" | 2017 !! data-sort-type="number" | 2016 |- | 1 | {{flag|China}} | 2,220,430 | 2,380,256 |- | 2 | {{flag|India}} | 305,000 | 277,000 |- | 3 | {{flag|Russia}} | 188,251 | 214,449 |- | 4 | {{flag|Poland}} | 176,352 | 177,203 |- | 5 | {{flag|Turkey}} | 175,357 | 173,394 |- | 6 | {{flag|United States}} | 130,710 | 131,160 |- | 7 | {{flag|Iran}} | 119,528 | 151,645 |- | 8 | {{flag|Uzbekistan}} | 94,517 | 95,405 |- | 9 | {{flag|Ukraine}} | 91,200 | 91,600 |- | 10 | {{flag|Pakistan}} | 78,302 | 90,607 |- |}
